# Commit Message Conventions

## Commit Message Format

Follow the Conventional Commits specification with emoji icons for all commit messages:

```
<emoji> <type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>  <!-- Only for complex commits that need explanation -->

<footer>  <!-- Only for complex commits (issue references, breaking changes) -->
```

**Keep commit messages short and brief.** The subject line should be self-explanatory. Only add body and footer for large, complex commits that cannot be understood from the subject alone.

