## Rules for AI Commit Message Generation

When generating commit messages:

1. Always use the conventional commit format with emoji icons
2. Start with the appropriate emoji for the commit type
3. Choose the most appropriate type based on the changes
4. Include scope when it's clear what component/area is affected
5. **Keep commit messages short and brief** - prefer single-line commits
6. Write clear, concise subject lines (max 72 chars) that are self-explanatory
7. **Only add body/footer for large, complex commits** that cannot be understood from the subject alone
8. Use present tense, imperative mood
9. Be specific about what changed in the subject line
10. Use only the commonly used commit types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
11. **Default to short format** - only expand with body/footer when absolutely necessary

